				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm not sure you understand this...
<br />
DC = Dire Charm = Charming a mob from a zone that you are hunting in and making it you pet for a fixed duration.
<br />

<br />
Our pets aren't affected by dire charm at all. What is effected is our demand for dps spots in groups. When SOE was thinking of implementing the Improved Dire Charm AA, which would have raised the level of Mob capable of being DC, that would have severly hurt our desirability for groups. Who would want a mage over a druid when a druid would be capable of so much more DPS, along with all the other utility that a druid brings?
<br />

<br />
We want our pets to be the BEST PETS bar none. All the utility and defensive spells that we "gave up" for monster pets needs to be restored.  They need to FIX pet scaling so that mages can have a chance to survive in the content they play in.
<br />

<br />
But no, we don't need any more ideas for DC <img src="images/smiles/eusa_shhh.gif" alt="Shhh" border="0" /> 
<br />

