			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Why do mage pets have to be the best pets?  Excluding charmed pets of course, although I'd even be willing to consider that if charm could be fixed appropriately.
<br />

<br />
But seriously.  Why do mage pets *have* to be the *best*?  I don't get it, and no I'm not trolling.
<br />

<br />
(At least I hope not...heh)
<br />

<br />
I understand concern about falling behind in terms of your primary role in a group (DPS).  That makes sense to me.
<br />

<br />
I understand wanting the primary focus of your offense and defense to be your pets.  This also makes sense to me.
<br />

<br />
But if the decision is made to make the primary focus of the offfense and defense of the three primary pet-classes in the game (magician, necromancer, and beastlord) their respective pets, then the argument in my mind that any of those classes should have the "best pet" breaks down as silly and bad for game balance.  What instead makes more sense is that pet + other stuff for all three classes, if we had a perfect system for scoring both, should be roughly equal among all three.
<br />

<br />
The devil is, of course, in the details.  But still that balance does not *require* magician pets to be the best.  That's one possible implementation of course, but its not the only one.<br />_________________<br />EQ1: Zarros (65 cleric), Saryrn Server
<br />
EQ1: Zanros (65 beastlord), Saryrn Server
<br />
CoH: Tachyon Trinity (23 blaster), Virtue</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
